item.description:
Probability theory deals with quantities and events that are distributed randomly and shows how to calculate average values of various kinds.
Discrete Distributions We denote some variable of interest as $x$ and the discrete values that it may take as $x_i$ ($i = 1, 2, &hellip;, N$). If the probability that $x_i$ occurs is $p_i$, then the mean value (or expectation value) of $x$ is:
\begin{equation}
\langle x \rangle = \sum_{i=1}^{N}x_ip_i \end{equation}
